abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Sept. 26--The Philadelphia Phillies captured Round One of the great shootout tonight when they defeated the Montreal Expos, 2-1, on a ninth-inning home run by Bake McBride.

abstract: PHILADELPHIA, Sept. 24--Pete Rose, who had been hitless in his last 15 times at bat, connected with a Neil Allen fastball for a single that drove in Jay Loviglio in the 10th inning and gave the Philadelphia Phillies a 1-0 victory over the New York Mets tonight.
byline_original: By Thomas Rogers Special To the New York Times

abstract: CHICAGO, Sept. 23 Mike Krukow, a 28-year-old right-hander, was toiling smoothly, holding the Mets to three hits for eight innings and enjoying a 6-0 lead today.

abstract: BIRMINGHAM, Ala., Sept. 23 (UPI)  Jim Folsom Jr., son of former Gov. James Folsom of Alabama, defeated United States Senator Donald W. Stewart today in a close race in a runoff election for the Democratic Senate nomination.
headline_main: Folsom Defeats Senator Stewart In Alabama's Democratic Runoff

abstract: MINOT, N.D.--The Air Force, traditionally a highly trained military service that had its pick of technical personnel, is losing skilled mid-level enlisted people as well as pilots and navigators at a time when the service's role has been expanded to focus on the Persian Gulf.

abstract: OVER the public-address system at Shea Stadium yesterday, those of the 50,608 spectators who remained were informed that Richard Todd's 35th completion had just broken the one-game Jet record set by Joe Namath in 1970. Not long after that, it was announced that Richard Todd had just tied the National Football League ...
Against a background of ironic circumstances, the Jets, who have not won, face the San Francisco 49ers, who have not lost, today at Shea Stadium.
headline_main: The 0-2 Jets Get Ready; for Pass-to-Backs 49ers, 2-0 The Short-Pass Game Walker Should Be Ready

abstract: SOUTH BEND, Ind., Sept. 20-- Harry Oliver, a left-footed place-kicker from Cincinnati, became one of the biggest heroes in recent Notre Dame football today when he booted a 51-yard field goal as time ran out to give the Fighting Irish a 29-27 victory over Michigan.
headline_main: Irish Win, 29-27, On Kick at Finish; Kiel Connects With Hunter Notre Dame Beats Michigan on Final Play Wangler Takes Over Irish Go Ahead, 26-21
